As Talent Acquisition Manager, I owned the Talent programs and initiatives for Australia and New Zealand, focusing on constantly lifting our talent capability as we continue our transformative online journey. The role had a strong commercial focus, ensuring efficient and cost effective delivery.


My role was also responsible for:

*Meeting annual direct recruitment savings targets;
*Meeting of time to hire and cost per hire metrics;
*Setting and executing the MYOB Talent Roadmap;
*Designing and maintaining a successful Employment Brand;
*Developing and embedding MYOB's Employee Value Proposition (EVP);
*Design and delivery of Good Practice Recruitment training;
*Building and maintaining strong relationships with our suppliers across ANZ.

As a team, our purpose was to ensure a consistent and on-brand experience for our candidates whilst enabling our hiring managers to acquire the very best talent. We aimed to deliver new ways to hire and maximize our networks whilst spreading the word about our brand and the brilliant products MYOB delivers to our customers in Australia and New Zealand. We aligned with the business's culture of continuous improvement and LEAN principles and were trusted advisors to our Executive and senior leaders.
